AWS instance

Launch instance
Name; MyWebServer
Instance Type: t2.micro or t3.micro
Key pair:
Key  pair name : my-key
Key pair type : RSA
Private key file format : .pem

Launch Instance

Inside Amazon Web Services console:
1. Go to EC2
2. Click your running instance
3. Click Connect (top right)
4. Choose EC2 Instance Connect
5. Click Connect
👉 A browser-based terminal opens

sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd

Step 4: Upload Sample Webpage
Go to web directory:

cd /var/www/html

Create a sample page:

sudo nano index.html

Paste:

<html>
<head><title>My EC2 Website</title></head>
<body>
<h1>Hello from EC2 🎉</h1>
<p>This is my sample webpage hosted on AWS.</p>
</body>
</html>

Save: Ctrl + X → Y → Enter

🌍 Step 5: View Website
* Copy your Public IPv4 address
* Open browser:

http://<your-public-ip>
